    <article>
        <articleInfo lang="EN" FirstPage="121" LastPage="130">
            <pdf>26207-jdecp-omeike.pdf</pdf>
            <abstract>This paper investigates the asymptotic stability of the zero solution of some
                system of linear delay differential equations with diagonal delay. By constructing
                a Lyapunov functional and using the Lyapunov-Krasovskii method, sufficient criteria
                which ensure the asymptotic stability of the zero solution are established. The local
                asymptotic stability of a positive equilibrium of the Lotka-Volterra systems is
                investigated to demonstrate our results.</abstract>
            <title>Asymptotic Stability of Linear Differential Equations with Diagonal Delay Via the Lyapunov-Krasovskii Method</title>
            <keywords>
                <word>Asymptotic stability</word>
                <word>Delay differential equations</word>
                <word>Diagonal delay</word>
                <word>Lyapunov-Krasovskii method</word>
                <word>Stability criteria</word>
            </keywords>
