    <article>
        <articleInfo lang="EN" FirstPage="131" LastPage="152">
            <pdf>26208-jdecp-averina.pdf</pdf>
            <abstract>In this paper, an algorithm for modeling projection estimates of distributions using Legendre polynomials is constructed for systems with a random structure, distributed transitions, and constant intensities.
                The accuracy of the projection estimates is investigated. A mathematical model for the problem of smoothing a random binary signal with an aperiodic link is used as a test model.
                This model reflects the essence of  physical processes occurring in systems with a random structure.</abstract>
            <title>Projection Estimation of Distributions in the Analysis of Systems with Random Structure</title>
            <keywords>
                <word>Legendre polynomials</word>
                <word>Monte-Carlo methods</word>
                <word>stochastic differential equations</word>
                <word>systems with random structure</word>
            </keywords>
